  <description><![CDATA[<p>The Chaberton Lodge &amp; Spa is close to the centre of <a data-udi="umb://document/a0b1d3c577424320a9af2e1af08b6887" href="/{localLink:umb://document/a0b1d3c577424320a9af2e1af08b6887}" title="Sauze d'Oulx">Sauze d'Oulx</a> and offers superb quality accommodation. It's got stunning views of the surrounding mountains and valley and has a lovely, warm ambience throughout. Enjoy nightly entertainment in the lounge area or relax and enjoy a drink or two in the bar area.  </p>
<h2>Shuttle service</h2>
<p>There's a free shuttle bus at set times to get you to and from the lifts or you can jump on the local ski bus that stops less than a minute away. If you want to head to the centre of Sauze, it is about a five minute walk through the old town, you can then find a range of shops, cosy restaurants and lively bars. </p>
<h2>Food and drink</h2>
<p>After a day of exploring the <a data-udi="umb://document/342fdefebf5f411d9f973a480753767c" href="/{localLink:umb://document/342fdefebf5f411d9f973a480753767c}" title="Milky Way Ski Area">Milky Way Ski Area</a>, there's plenty to keep you occupied. Head to the Lounge Bar after a day on the mountain and cosy up in front of the fireplace with a drink, or catch up with friends and family before dinner with a classic aperitivo. When the sun is out, the terrace area is a lovely spot to soak up some winter sun. You can enjoy delicious meals in the cosy restaurant, breakfast will prepare you for a day on the slopes and when you return you can enjoy tasty homemade dishes from with Piedmont region. The hotel has a wonderful wine cellar, speak to the Sommelier for their recommendations - wine tasting experiences can be booked through the reception, where you can learn more about the wines and even sample a few (pay locally). After a tasty evening meal spend your evenings in Club Chaberton, where you can enjoy live music and DJ sets. </p>
<h2>Spa area</h2>
<p>We recommend taking some time out to relax in the hotel's spa (payable locally). Soothe any achy ski legs in the whirlpool, head outside the the outdoor 'Tinozza' tub with mountain views before warming up in the sauna or steam room. If you are wanting to stay active, even off of the slopes, there is also a fitness room with a range of equipment available for you to use. And for the ultimate treat, massages are available for a little extra fee.</p>]]></description>
